==English==
===Intransitive verb===
'''to lone it'''
# to go alone.
*'''1955-1956:''' Allen Ginsberg, ''Howl'' - who loned it through the streets of Idaho seeking visionary indian angels who were visionary indian angels
*'''1967:''' S.E. Hinton, ''The Outsiders'' - I had a long walk home and no company, but I usually lone it anyway, for no reason except that I like to watch movies undisturbed so I can get into them and live them with the actors. &hellip; So I loned it.
